RACE.RACE_TEXT: Fred W. Hooper S. presented by Whispering Angel - Grade3 GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 10 1M Dirt CR: 105. Stakes Purse 150000. FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Free nomination by Saturday, January 14. $1,500 to enter. $150,000 Guaranteed. A supplemental nomination fee of $100 may be made prior to closing time of entries. After payment of 1% to all owners of horses finishing sixth throu gh last, 62% of the remaining purse shall be paid to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 10% to third, 5% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weight: 124 lbs. Non-winners of a graded stakes since July 1 allowed 2 lbs.; a graded stakes race in 2022-23, 4 lbs.; three races other than maiden, claiming, starter or state-bred allowance race, 6 lbs. Starters to be named by usual time of closing. All fees shall be paid prior to the start of the race. Preference will be given to graded stakes winners in 2021-23, gra ded stakes placed since then, then by highest career earnings. Trophy to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ENDORSED raced in midpack from the four path, was under right handed urging while ranging up from the eight path into the lane, rallied and drew past inner foes inside the final furlong to win clearly. OCTANE brushed with an inner foe leaving the gate, stalked along the inside, was coaxed from the two path turning into the stretch, and ran on for place. DEAN DELIVERS tracked in the four path, was roused around the turn and driven from the six path into the stretch, and kept on under left handed urging for show. NOBLE DRAMA trailed along the inside, moved up around the turn, angled out to the six path going into the lane, and finished evenly. PREVALENCE prompted the pace in the three path, was under left handed urging from the four path turning into the stretch, but yielded in the final furlong. BLACK BELT bumped an inner foe out of the gate, raced prominently in the three path, was driven from the five path into the stretch, but flattened. MILES D raced from wellback in the two path, shifted out to the seven path turning into the lane, but was no factor. MISH had an awkward start and brushed with an outer foe, chased in the four path, fanned out to the nine path into the stretch, but never threatened. PICKING UP PENNIES bumped with an outer foe at the start, set the pace in the two path, but gaveway along the inside turning into the stretch. THE REDS rated in the four path, tipped out to the eight path turning into the stretch, but was tired. TWELVE VOLT MAN stumbled at the start and was hustled along in the six path, but was not a threat. DOC AMSTER got bumped by an inner foe into an outer foe leaving the gate, was behind in the four path and never menaced.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Pegasus World Cup Invitational S. presented by Baccarat - Grade1 GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 13 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 111. Stakes Purse 3000000. FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ART COLLECTOR settled in range four wide, edged closer outside down the backstretch, gained three deep around the far turn, took over in upper stretch and readily drew off under a drive. DEFUNDED pressed the pace three wide between foes around the first turn and two wide between rivals around the far turn, reached near even terms inside of the winner approaching the quarter pole, could not match strides with that foe in upper stretch but kept to hold clear of the rest. STILLETO BOY set the pace along the rail to upper stretch, could not keep pace with winner from there but kept trying at the rail to hold third. LAST SAMURAI settled off the pace while racing two wide between foes, edged closer down the backstretch, remained in range two wide between around the far turn, angled four wide in upper stretch and churned on to hold fourth. PROXY saved ground off the pace, remained well back in the two path rounding the far turn, swung out in upper stretch and made a mild rally. CYBERKNIFE raced off the pace three wide around the first turn, was urged along four wide around the far turn and lacked a serious response. SKIPPYLONGSTOCKING raced in range four wide, crept closer four wide under a drive around the far turn but had little left for the drive. WHITE ABARRIO had early speed two wide between foes around the first turn, chased inside down the backstretch and around the far turn and came up empty in the lane. GET HER NUMBER was in a bit tight early, raced off the pace four and five wide and never threatened. SIMPLIFICATION saved ground in range, dropped back a bit inside around the far turn, swung six wide nearing the quarter pole and retreated. O'CONNOR (CHI) played no factor while racing four wide. RIDIN WITH BIDEN checked nearing the first turn, trailed in the two path and was eased in the lane.
